review_blob: Right now, if I could drink one beer this would be it. Beautiful nearly orange clear color with full white head. Floral and citrus bouquet nose. Perfect bitter to sweet hop to malt balance
beer_name: Creature Comforts Tropiclia

review_blob: Received in trade. Got my New Mexico tick. Surprised how few rates are on here. I would call this a deep ruby IIPA.
beer_name: La Cumbre Red Ryeot

review_blob: Underrated beer. Dont always care for Terrapins distribution system in state, but this beer is bloody brilliant. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Terrapin Wake-n-Bake Coffee Oatmeal Imperial Stout

review_blob: My dad continues to crush it on the beer selection. Sour with grape tones. Live and fun. Bottle - Shared by Dad
beer_name: Crooked Stave St. Bretta (Winter)

review_blob: Drank past the best buy date. Held up. Nice bretty candy scent. Live and delicious. Bottle - Shared by Dad
beer_name: Deschutes Foray Belgian Style IPA

review_blob: Thanks to my Dad for bringing this back from the brewery. Pours darkest brown with red tinge and light tan head. Scent is smoky candy. Sweet to earth flavor. Bottle - Shared by Dad
beer_name: Three Floyds Moloko Plus

review_blob: Thanks to Andy for ordering this out of the Porters cellar. Maple syrup on the nose and in the taste. Fizzled than expected, which I love. Bottle - Porter Beer Bar - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: The Bruery Cuivre

review_blob: From the Vault Rate #2. Pretty sparse notes here. Synthetic. Biting. Average.
beer_name: Revolution Mother of Exiles

review_blob: From the Vault Rate #1. Candy & Caramel. Pours a clear dark amber. Medium Heavy Body.
beer_name: Swamp Head / Cigar City Roosevelt American Barley Wine - Barrel Aged

review_blob: Another amazing Westbrook offering. Same coloration and head as other variants. Chocolate enhanced by Bourbon. Bottle - Shared at BSP
beer_name: Westbrook Mexican Cake Imperial Stout - Bourbon Barrel (2014)

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Been waiting a long time on this brew. Worth it. Hazy pale gold. Peachy sour flavor. Live in the mouth. Bottle - Shared at BSP
beer_name: Lost Abbey Duck Duck Gooze

review_blob: Same coloration and head as other variants. Rye bitterness is more of a detractor than enhancer. Still a best in class Imperial Stout. Bottle - Shared at BSP
beer_name: Westbrook Mexican Cake Imperial Stout - Double Barrel

review_blob: Dark with tan head. Tequila blends well with the peppery nose. Nice spice / earth / chocolate blend. Bottle - Shared at BSP.
beer_name: Westbrook Mexican Cake Imperial Stout - Tequila Barrel

review_blob: Interesting beer. Pours a touch more copper that what I would consider a classic IPA. Scent is resinous. Flavor is unusual in that it has a strong spicy pepper element, despite no peppers being used in the brew. Odd. Draft - Brick Store Pub - Decatur, Georgia
beer_name: Sweetwater Hop Hash Double IPA

review_blob: Nice affordable available option. Bought a bunch for a party. Pours coppers with decent head. Nice light hop and light sweet flavor. Bottle - Dekalb Farmers Market - Decatur, GA
beer_name: New Belgium Tour de Fall

review_blob: Grabbed this while in Charleston. Pours copper with thick off white head. Scent is a touch of citrus and grain. A little hop forward for my liking. Would like a bit more balance. Bottle - Bottles - Charleston, SC
beer_name: Maine Beer Red Wheelbarrow

review_blob: Enjoyed several of these during the Georgia-Clemson Tailgate. Refreshing in the hot weather. Low in alcohol for a long day. Poured a pinkish straw. Lively, crisp, and delicious. The barely there hint of sweetness makes this beer. Will seek out in the future. Bottle - Ale Yeah! - Decatur, GA
beer_name: Boulevard Hibiscus Gose

review_blob: This beer has been sitting in my fridge tempting me for months. Pours dark chocolate with appropriate amount of dark tan head. Scent is like a mocha coffee. Flavor goes sweet to mildly bitter. Thickish with medium carbonation. Bottle - Received in Trade
beer_name: Almanac Biere de Chocolat

review_blob: Free beer. Gets me my 39th state rating. Not a blonde ale fan. This didnt change my mind. Pours straw color. Highly carbonated with a bitter bite. Bottle - Source Unknown
beer_name: Kona Big Wave Golden Ale

review_blob: First Ive heard of Quest. Damn Good Beer, but I am a sucker for Belgian Pale Ale. Bretty scent. Golden have color. Earthy sweet flavor throughout. Draft - Closed for Business - Charleston, SC
beer_name: Quest Golden Fleece Belgian Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours nearly black with thin brown head. Fantastic coffee and earth scent leads to disappointing flavor. Thin bodied and flat. Draft - Closed for Business - Charleston, SC
beer_name: Grand Teton Black Cauldron Imperial Stout

review_blob: Jealous that this beer is apparently just lying on the shelves here in Charleston. Pours darkest brown with tan head. Scent is coffee and Reeses Peanut Butter Cup. Sweet front mild bite back. Thick. Bottle - Bottles - Mt. Pleasant, SC
beer_name: Maine Beer King Titus

review_blob: Coast comes correct. Pours lovely dark straw with white head. Scent is candy and mild hops. Nicely carbonated. Bottle - Bottles - Charleston, SC
beer_name: COAST All Chinook Pale Ale

review_blob: Underwhelmed. Pours clear dark straw. Scent is soapy dish rag. Flavor is overly bitter. Live. Draft - Westbrook Brewing - Charleston, SC
beer_name: Evil Twin Femme Fatale Sudachi

review_blob: Wish I had this on the beach instead of after. Hazy pale yellow. Lemony berry taste. Lively. Draft - Westbrook Brewing - Mt. Pleasant, SC
beer_name: Evil Twin Nomader Weisse

review_blob: Got this Charleston weekend kicked off right. Nice scent. Great citrus flavor. Hazy and bubbly. Can - Bi Lo - Isle of Palms, SC
beer_name: Holy City Washout Wheat

review_blob: Best in show from the Beer Camp Series. Truly delicious. Might rather have bought a full 12 pack of this brew. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, Georgia
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Ninkasi Beer Camp Double Latte

review_blob: This might be the best of the Beer Camp Beers. Scent is candy citrus. Flavor goes bitter to sweet. IPA tendencies. Good stuff. Can - Ale Yeah! - Decatur, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Oskar Blues Beer Camp CANfusion Rye Bock

review_blob: Pours darkest brown with nice tan head. Scent is burnt booze with hints of chocolate. Booze all over flavor. Not enough flavor notes to overcome the booze. Bottle - Ale Yeah! - Decatur, GA
beer_name: Evil Twin I Love You With My Stout

review_blob: These Beer Camp Beers seem to be dominating Ratebeer. This was damn good beer, but I think the hype effect was in play. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Cigar City Beer Camp Yonder Bock

review_blob: Pours dark amber with off white head. Bready scent. Mild sweet to bitter taste. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Victory Beer Camp Alt Route

review_blob: Would like to have gotten this a little fresher. Booze dominates the scent and flavor. A touch dark for style. Good beer. Was hoping for more. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Ballast Point Beer Camp Electric Ray

review_blob: Solid pilsner. Pours clear straw with rapidly dissipating white head. Scent is hay up front with touch of hops. Not the best hopped up Pilsner Ive had, but damn good. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Firestone Walker Beer Camp Torpedo Pilsner

review_blob: Perfect for style. Copper color with off white head. Bready aroma with a hardly detectable hint of hops. Mildly sweet and earthy throughout. Would love to try this on cask. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / New Glarus Beer Camp There And Back

review_blob: Had 4 beers at Wrecking Bar. This beers rating may be a function of it being the worst of the 4. Draft - Wrecking Bar - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Wrecking Bar La Flamme Blanche IPA

review_blob: Was as excited for this beer as any in the pack. Underwhelmed. Poured clear light gold with rapidly dissipating white head. Banana and clove scent. Brett sweet flavor. Thin bodied. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Russian River Beer Camp Yvan the Great

review_blob: Earlier rate referred to this beer as a kitchen sink brew. Apropos. Pours darkest brown with nice tan head. Scent is spice, chocolate, coffee, and caramel. Flavor is sweet with a spicy bite. Thick. Draft - Wrecking Bar, Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Wrecking Bar / Ale Yeah Border Patrol Hot Pursuit

review_blob: Poured clear straw with quickly dissipating white head. Scent is mild grain. Tart with hint of fruit flavor. Light bodied and brisk. Draft - Wrecking Bar - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Wrecking Bar Another Brick Berliner Weisse

review_blob: Pours dark amber with off white head. Grainy scent. Faded hops up front. Light medium body with mild carbonation. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Three Floyds Beer Camp Chico King

review_blob: Dark brown with lasting pale brown head. Toffee, booze, and a touch of citrus scent. Sweet and earthy up front with astringent finish. Medium and live. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Asheville Brewers Alliance Beer Camp Tater Ridge

review_blob: Jalapeno scent on the nose was interesting. Heat in the flavor seemed unbalanced. Thinking style and peppers dont mix. Color and palate were exemplars of style. Draft - Ale Yeah! - Decatur, GA
beer_name: Ballast Point Habanero Sculpin

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: This is a numbers only rating. My chicken scratch notes are not much help. Thanks for the share. Mustve liked it.
beer_name: Hair of the Dog Adam

review_blob: Was odd to see so many low rates of this beer. Bottle I shared with Westmeister was fanatastic. Bottle - Receive in Trade
beer_name: Ale Industries East Bayliner Weisse

review_blob: Dont remember much about this beer other than my numeric rating. Best thing about it might be the name and label. Bottle - Received in Trade
beer_name: Pipeworks Hey, Careful Man, Theres a Beverage Here!

review_blob: Poured dark for style with limited head. Fizzy and fun for low ABV beer. Bottle - Ale Yeah! - Decatur, GA
beer_name: Red Brick Dog Days Hefeweizen

review_blob: Other unnamed sites call this a Kolsch. A watered down Saison seems more accurate. Drinkable not memorable.
beer_name: Back Forty Fence Post Session Ale

review_blob: Freshness uncertain. Pours black with small head. No hop character to balance roasted malts. Over carbonated.
beer_name: Uinta Dubhe Imperial Black IPA

review_blob: I am a sucker for Belgian Pale Ale. Pours hazy gold with appropriate head. Scent is spicy as is flavor. Sweet and earthy. Lively on the tongue.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Allagash Beer Camp Myrons Walk

review_blob: Regular Tasting Group Share. Had the Apple Brandy awhile ago. Been holding this. This balances better than the apple brandy. Bourbon gives nice savory balance. Bottle - Greens on Ponce - Atlanta, GA
beer_name: Westbrook Siberian Black Magic Panther - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Pours hazy pale yellow with white head. Scent is bretty and fruity and lovely. Live in the mouth. Terrific. Bottle - Shared by jrob21
beer_name: Hill Farmstead Civil Disobedience (Release 6)
